```

---

### 🟡 9. Plain HTTP — No TLS Enforcement (OWASP A02)

The server listens on port 3000 over plain HTTP. Any data transmitted — including future auth tokens — travels unencrypted.

**Recommendation:** TLS should be terminated at the reverse proxy (nginx/load balancer) level in production. If running standalone:
